Hi All,
When I do a modprobe ibmtr in Kernel version 2.3.31 to activate it, my
server crashes.
The panic starts with:
eip: c18092f4
kernel BUG at /usr/src/linux/include/asm/spinlock.h:78!
invalid operand: 0000
CPU:    0
EIP:      0010:[<c1809320>]
EFLAGS: 00010286
I don't see an OOPS code on the screen.
Has anyone seen this problem? I had the same problem with kernel 2.3.30.
Regards,
Richard van Denzel.
